## Background

Effective observability requires proactive alerting when important events occur in the system. Users should not need to constantly monitor dashboards to stay informed about agent status changes, cost anomalies, conflict resolutions, or system issues. A comprehensive notification system bridges this gap by delivering relevant information through the user's preferred channels.

## Problem Statement

Currently, users must manually check the platform to discover issues or important events. This leads to delayed responses to critical situations (agent failures, cost overruns, conflicts requiring approval) and reduces overall platform effectiveness. Different users have different notification preferences - some prefer email digests while others need real-time Slack alerts for urgent issues.

