## Acceptance Criteria

- [ ] Fleet management: add, remove, list, filter repos
- [ ] Fleet stats calculate correct counts
- [ ] Sync operations track progress and publish events
- [ ] Sync can be cancelled mid-operation
- [ ] Agent sweep creates session and orchestrates phases
- [ ] Phase progression tracked with timestamps
- [ ] Plans stored with validation and risk assessment
- [ ] Plan approval/rejection workflow works
- [ ] Execution only runs approved plans
- [ ] All events published via WebSocket
- [ ] All unit tests pass with comprehensive logging

## Problem Statement

The Gateway needs real-time WebSocket event streaming for RU operations so the frontend can display live progress updates for sync operations and agent-sweep sessions.

## Background

RU operations are long-running:
- Fleet sync can take minutes for large fleets
- Agent-sweep has three phases, each with per-repo progress
- Users need to see live updates without polling

The Gateway already has a WebSocket hub infrastructure. We need to:
1. Define RU-specific event types
2. Publish events from RU services
3. Create subscription channels for fleet, sync, and sweep

