# Task: Implement Rate Limit Headers Middleware

## Parent Epic
[Epic] Rate Limit Headers (flywheel_gateway-dkz)

## Objective
Create middleware that tracks request rates and includes rate limit headers in all responses.

## Deliverables

### 1. Rate Limit Types
```typescript
// apps/gateway/src/middleware/rate-limit.ts

export interface RateLimitConfig {
  /** Maximum requests per window */
  limit: number;
  /** Window size in milliseconds */
  windowMs: number;
  /** Key generator function */
  keyGenerator: (c: Context) => string;
}

export interface RateLimitInfo {
  /** Total limit */
  limit: number;
  /** Remaining requests */
  remaining: number;
  /** Unix timestamp when window resets */
  reset: number;
}
```

### 2. In-Memory Rate Limiter
```typescript
class InMemoryRateLimiter {
  private counters: Map<string, { count: number; resetAt: number }> = new Map();

  check(key: string, config: RateLimitConfig): RateLimitInfo {
    const now = Date.now();
    let entry = this.counters.get(key);

    // Reset if window expired
    if (!entry || entry.resetAt <= now) {
      entry = {
        count: 0,
        resetAt: now + config.windowMs,
      };
    }

    entry.count++;
    this.counters.set(key, entry);

    return {
      limit: config.limit,
      remaining: Math.max(0, config.limit - entry.count),
      reset: Math.ceil(entry.resetAt / 1000),
    };
  }

  isLimited(key: string, config: RateLimitConfig): boolean {
    const entry = this.counters.get(key);
    if (!entry || entry.resetAt <= Date.now()) return false;
    return entry.count > config.limit;
  }
}
```

### 3. Hono Middleware
```typescript
import { Context, Next } from "hono";

const rateLimiter = new InMemoryRateLimiter();

export function rateLimitMiddleware(config: RateLimitConfig) {
  return async (c: Context, next: Next) => {
    const key = config.keyGenerator(c);

    // Check if limited
    if (rateLimiter.isLimited(key, config)) {
      const info = rateLimiter.check(key, config);

      c.header("X-RateLimit-Limit", String(info.limit));
      c.header("X-RateLimit-Remaining", "0");
      c.header("X-RateLimit-Reset", String(info.reset));
      c.header("Retry-After", String(info.reset - Math.ceil(Date.now() / 1000)));

      return c.json({
        error: {
          code: "RATE_LIMIT_EXCEEDED",
          message: "Rate limit exceeded",
          retryAfter: info.reset - Math.ceil(Date.now() / 1000),
        },
      }, 429);
    }

    // Process request
    await next();

    // Add rate limit headers to response
    const info = rateLimiter.check(key, config);
    c.header("X-RateLimit-Limit", String(info.limit));
    c.header("X-RateLimit-Remaining", String(info.remaining));
    c.header("X-RateLimit-Reset", String(info.reset));
  };
}
```

### 4. Key Generators
```typescript
/** Rate limit by IP address */
export function byIP(c: Context): string {
  return c.req.header("X-Forwarded-For")?.split(",")[0] 
    ?? c.req.header("X-Real-IP") 
    ?? "unknown";
}

/** Rate limit by API key */
export function byAPIKey(c: Context): string {
  return c.req.header("Authorization")?.replace("Bearer ", "") ?? byIP(c);
}

/** Rate limit by user ID (from auth context) */
export function byUser(c: Context): string {
  return c.get("userId") ?? byAPIKey(c);
}
```

### 5. Configure Per-Route Limits
```typescript
// Apply different limits to different routes
app.use("/agents", rateLimitMiddleware({
  limit: 100,
  windowMs: 60000,  // 100 req/min
  keyGenerator: byAPIKey,
}));

app.use("/agents/*/send", rateLimitMiddleware({
  limit: 30,
  windowMs: 60000,  // 30 msg/min per agent
  keyGenerator: (c) => `${byAPIKey(c)}:${c.req.param("agentId")}`,
}));
```

## Headers Returned
| Header | Description | Example |
|--------|-------------|---------|
| X-RateLimit-Limit | Max requests per window | 100 |
| X-RateLimit-Remaining | Remaining in window | 95 |
| X-RateLimit-Reset | Unix timestamp of reset | 1704931200 |
| Retry-After | Seconds until retry (on 429) | 42 |

