## Problem Statement

The Gateway database has placeholder tables for RU (Repo Updater) integration that don't match the actual data structures needed. These need to be completely redesigned to support fleet status, sync operations, and agent-sweep workflows.

## Background

RU (Repo Updater) is a production-grade Bash CLI for managing large collections of GitHub repositories. Key data structures needed:

1. **Fleet Repositories** - All repos being managed
2. **Sync Operations** - Clone/pull history and status
3. **Agent Sweep Sessions** - Multi-phase automated maintenance runs
4. **Agent Sweep Plans** - JSON plans produced by agents
5. **Agent Sweep Executions** - Plan execution results

Current placeholder schema is inadequate:

```typescript
// Existing (insufficient)
export const fleetRepos = sqliteTable("fleet_repos", {
  id: text("id").primaryKey(),
  name: text("name").notNull(),
  // ... minimal fields
});
```

## Implementation Plan

### 1. Fleet Repositories Table

```typescript
// apps/gateway/src/db/schema.ts

export const fleetRepos = sqliteTable("fleet_repos", {
  id: text("id").primaryKey(),

  // Repository identification
  owner: text("owner").notNull(),           // GitHub owner/org
  name: text("name").notNull(),             // Repository name
  fullName: text("full_name").notNull(),    // owner/name
  url: text("url").notNull(),               // Clone URL
  sshUrl: text("ssh_url"),                  // SSH URL

  // Local state
  localPath: text("local_path"),            // Where it's cloned
  isCloned: integer("is_cloned", { mode: "boolean" }).default(false),

  // Git state
  currentBranch: text("current_branch"),
  defaultBranch: text("default_branch"),
  lastCommit: text("last_commit"),          // SHA
  lastCommitDate: integer("last_commit_date", { mode: "timestamp" }),
  lastCommitAuthor: text("last_commit_author"),

  // Status
  status: text("status").default("unknown"), // healthy|dirty|behind|ahead|diverged|unknown
  hasUncommittedChanges: integer("has_uncommitted_changes", { mode: "boolean" }).default(false),
  hasUnpushedCommits: integer("has_unpushed_commits", { mode: "boolean" }).default(false),
  aheadBy: integer("ahead_by").default(0),
  behindBy: integer("behind_by").default(0),

  // Metadata
  description: text("description"),
  language: text("language"),
  stars: integer("stars"),
  isPrivate: integer("is_private", { mode: "boolean" }),
  isArchived: integer("is_archived", { mode: "boolean" }),

  // RU integration
  ruGroup: text("ru_group"),                // Grouping for batch operations
  ruConfig: text("ru_config"),              // JSON config overrides
  agentsmdPath: text("agentsmd_path"),      // Path to AGENTS.md if exists
  lastScanDate: integer("last_scan_date", { mode: "timestamp" }),

  // Timestamps
  addedAt: integer("added_at", { mode: "timestamp" }).default(sql`(unixepoch())`),
  updatedAt: integer("updated_at", { mode: "timestamp" }),
  lastSyncAt: integer("last_sync_at", { mode: "timestamp" }),
}, (table) => ({
  ownerIdx: index("fleet_repos_owner_idx").on(table.owner),
  statusIdx: index("fleet_repos_status_idx").on(table.status),
  groupIdx: index("fleet_repos_group_idx").on(table.ruGroup),
  fullNameUnique: unique("fleet_repos_full_name_unique").on(table.fullName),
}));
```

### 2. Sync Operations Table

```typescript
export const fleetSyncOps = sqliteTable("fleet_sync_ops", {
  id: text("id").primaryKey(),

  // Target
  repoId: text("repo_id").references(() => fleetRepos.id),
  repoFullName: text("repo_full_name").notNull(),

  // Operation type
  operation: text("operation").notNull(),   // clone|pull|fetch|push

  // Status
  status: text("status").notNull(),         // pending|running|success|failed|cancelled

  // Results
  startedAt: integer("started_at", { mode: "timestamp" }),
  completedAt: integer("completed_at", { mode: "timestamp" }),
  durationMs: integer("duration_ms"),

  // Git details
  fromCommit: text("from_commit"),          // Before sync
  toCommit: text("to_commit"),              // After sync
  commitCount: integer("commit_count"),     // Number of commits synced
  filesChanged: integer("files_changed"),

  // Error handling
  error: text("error"),
  errorCode: text("error_code"),
  retryCount: integer("retry_count").default(0),

  // Metadata
  triggeredBy: text("triggered_by"),        // user|schedule|agent-sweep
  correlationId: text("correlation_id"),    // For linking related ops

  createdAt: integer("created_at", { mode: "timestamp" }).default(sql`(unixepoch())`),
}, (table) => ({
